To build Alarmz, use qmake or Qt Creator. Use qmake CONFIG+=release for a
release build.

To generate the help files in HTML format from the source XML files, run
doc/generate-html.py. This script requires the lxml library
(http://codespeak.net/lxml/installation.html).

To install Alarmz on Windows, an NSIS install script is provided in the nsi/
subdirectory. Copy the following files in the nsi/ subdirectory before compiling
the installer:
- Alarmz.exe
- icudt*.dll
- icuin*.dll
- icuuc*.dll
- Qt5Core.dll
- Qt5Gui.dll
- Qt5Multimedia.dll
- Qt5Network.dll
- Qt5Widgets.dll
- Qt5Xml.dll
- Alarmz_fr.qm
- qt_fr.qm
- doc/style.css
- doc/en_US/addedit.html
- doc/en_US/alarms.html
- doc/en_US/index.html
- doc/en_US/license.html
- doc/en_US/menus.html
- doc/en_US/options.html
- doc/en_US/toasts.html
- doc/fr/addedit.html
- doc/fr/alarms.html
- doc/fr/index.html
- doc/fr/license.html
- doc/fr/menus.html
- doc/fr/options.html
- doc/fr/toasts.html
- qtaudio_windows.dll (copy from plugins/audio from Qt installation)
- qico.dll (copy from plugins/imageformats from Qt installation)
- qwindows.dll (copy from plugins/platforms from Qt installation)

If you are using Qt based on MinGW, you must also copy the following files from
the bin/ subdirectory of your MinGW installation:
- libgcc_s_dw2-1.dll
- libstdc++-6.dll
- libwinpthread-1.dll
